Russian Embassy in Jamaica:
On March 28, a meeting took place between the Russian delegation participating in the work of the Council of the International Seabed Authority (ISAU) and the Secretary General of the international organization M. Lodge.
Show more
The Secretary General, together with the head of the delegation, Deputy Minister of Natural Resources and Environment D.D. Tetenkin, discussed a number of issues, including:
the upcoming elections of the Secretary General of the organization;
Russians occupying positions in the structures of the Authority;
prospects for scientific cooperation in the field of deep-sea research;
participation of IOMD representatives in international specialized platforms and forums held in Russia.
According to M. Lodge, the Russian delegation makes a huge contribution to the work of the Authority; he also highly appreciates its constructive approach to resolving current issues of its activities. In turn, D.D. Tetenkin confirmed his intention to continue to cooperate with the IOMD, and also assured his partners of the further strengthening of Russian representation in the organization.
